{id:"spell-sunbeam",name:"Sunbeam",content:[{id:"Title",content:"Sunbeam"},{id:"StatGrid",content:[{title:"Level",content:"6"},{title:"Casting Time",content:"1 action"},{title:"Range",content:"Self (60ft line)"},{title:"Components",content:"V, S, M"},{title:"Duration",content:"Up to 1 minute"},{title:"School",content:"Evocation"},{title:"Save",content:"CON Save"},{title:"Damage",content:"Radiant"}]},{id:"Subtitle",content:"Effect"},{id:"MultiText",content:["A beam of brilliant light flashes out from your hand in a 5-foot-wide, 60-foot-long line. Each creature in the line must make a constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 6d8 radiant damage and is blinded until your next turn. On a successful save, it takes half as much damage and isn't blinded by this spell. Undead and oozes have disadvantage on this saving throw.","You can create a new line of radiance as your action on any turn until the spell ends.","For the duration, a mote of brilliant radiance shines in your hand. It sheds bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. This light is sunlight."]},{id:"Table",content:[["slot level","6"],["damage","6d8"]]}]}